<DOC><DOCNO> AP890721-0118 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-07-21-89 1619EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-Cambodia-Shelling     07-21 0208</FIRST><SECOND>AM-Cambodia-Shelling,0215</SECOND><HEAD>Refugee Camp Shelled; 1 Dead, 10 Wounded</HEAD><HEAD>With AM-Cambodia</HEAD><DATELINE>BANGKOK, Thailand (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Cambodian refugee camp run bycommunist Khmer Rouge guerrillas was hit by shelling Friday, andone refugee was killed and 10 were wounded, Western reliefofficials said.   It appeared the shells were fired by Cambodian government forcesor their Vietnamese allies, the relief officials said.   The three-hour attack followed overnight fighting in the area,according to a Thai security official, who spoke on condition ofanonymity.   The relief officials said about 27 rounds crashed into the Site8 camp, sending most of the 40,000 residents fleeing.   A 22-year-old man was killed and 10 refugees, including twochildren, were wounded, said an official of the InternationalCommittee of the Red Cross.   The camp in Thailand's eastern province of Prachinburi, about amile from the Cambodian border, is the main civilian camp run bythe Khmer Rouge, the largest guerrilla group fighting Cambodiangovernment forces and their Vietnamese allies.   The Khmer Rouge sometimes has shelled its own camps to exercisestrict control over the refugees. Widespread human rightsviolations have been reported in Khmer Rouge camps.   Fighting between Cambodian government forces and the Khmer Rougehas increased along the border in recent days.</TEXT></DOC>